@startuml
title Credential Revocation Lifecycle - Admin-initiated and Holder-requested (two cases, shared mechanism)

participant "Issuer Admin / Reviewer" as Admin
participant "Holder (Mobile Wallet)" as App #lightblue
participant "Issuer Portal / Backend" as Backend #lightgreen
participant "Credential Platform (Procivis Core)" as Core #orange
participant "HSM" as HSM #yellow

note over Backend,Core #wheat:[SPEC] Status model (POC = BITSTRINGSTATUSLIST)\nVALID -> SUSPENDED (temporary, optional suspendEndDate)\nVALID / SUSPENDED -> REVOKED (permanent, terminal)\nSUSPENDED -> VALID (reactivate)\nStatus List hosted by Core at /ssi/revocation/v1/list/{id}
note over Admin,App #wheat:[SPEC] TWO initiation paths in this file\nCASE A - Issuer Admin initiates the action directly\nCASE B - Holder REQUESTS revocation -> Issuer approves -> revoke\nBoth converge on the SHARED mechanism (Core changes status + re-publishes Status List)\nPrinciple: Holder may REQUEST ; only the Issuer can REVOKE (W3C VC 2.0)

alt CASE A : Issuer Admin initiates directly
==  CASE A : ADMIN / ISSUER INITIATES DIRECTLY  ==

    note over Admin,Backend #lightgreen: A1. Admin initiates lifecycle action
    Admin->Backend: action = REVOKE / SUSPEND / REACTIVATE\ncredentialId , reason
    Backend->Backend: Validate admin identity + authorization\npermission to manage this credential type / organisation
    Backend->Backend: Load credential reference\ncredentialId , statusListIndex , current status
    Backend->Backend: Validate state transition allowed\nREVOKE: from VALID/SUSPENDED , SUSPEND: from VALID , REACTIVATE: from SUSPENDED

    alt Invalid transition / unauthorized
        Backend->Backend: [ERROR AUDIT] Store failure\nfailureStep = VALIDATE_TRANSITION , reason , actorId , failedAt
        Backend-->Admin: Reject - invalid transition / insufficient permission
        note over Admin,Backend #pink: Outcome = NO ACTION (ends here)
    else Transition allowed
        note over Admin,Backend #lightgreen: decidedAction set -> proceed to SHARED below
    end

else CASE B : Holder requests revocation (request -> issuer approval)
==  CASE B : HOLDER REQUESTS  ->  ISSUER APPROVES  ==

    note over App,Backend #lightblue: B1. Holder submits a request (typed reason)
    App->Backend: Request revocation\ncredentialId , reasonType (LOST / STOLEN / COMPROMISED / NO_LONGER_NEEDED / DATA_ERROR) , reasonNote
    Backend->Backend: Validate holder owns credential\nnot already REVOKED , no PENDING request

    alt Already revoked / duplicate pending
        Backend->Backend: [ERROR AUDIT] Store failure\nfailureStep = VALIDATE_REQUEST , reason = already revoked / duplicate pending
        Backend-->App: Reject - already revoked or request pending
        note over App,Backend #pink: Outcome = NO ACTION (ends here)
    else Request accepted
        Backend->Backend: [DATA STORE] Create revocation request\nstatus = REQUESTED , reasonType , reasonNote , requestedAt , holderId
        Backend->Backend: [AUDIT LOG] Store revocation requested\neventType = REVOCATION_REQUESTED , holderId , reasonType

        note over Backend,Core #lightgreen: B2. Risk-based triage (NIST 800-63B)
        alt High risk - LOST / STOLEN / COMPROMISED
            note over Backend,Core #wheat:[SPEC] Fast-path: contain immediately, confirm later (reversible if false report)
            Backend->Core: Suspend immediately\n(POST /api/credential/v1/{id}/suspend)\nCore re-signs + re-publishes Status List (see SHARED)
            Backend->Backend: [AUDIT LOG] eventType = REVOCATION_FASTPATH_SUSPEND
            Backend-->App: Acknowledged - credential SUSPENDED immediately , under review
        else Low risk - NO_LONGER_NEEDED / DATA_ERROR
            Backend-->App: Acknowledged - request PENDING issuer review
        end

        note over Admin,Backend #lightgreen: B3. Issuer reviews within SLA (PDPA timeframe)
        Backend->Admin: Notify - pending revocation request
        note over Backend #wheat:[SPEC] SLA (PDPA): decide within the response window ; else escalation / default policy
        Admin->Backend: Review request (may re-verify holder identity / loss report)

        alt Issuer REJECTS
            Backend->Backend: [DATA STORE] Update request = REJECTED\nrejectReason (mandatory) , actionBy , actionAt
            opt Was fast-path suspended
                Backend->Core: Reactivate\n(POST /api/credential/v1/{id}/reactivate) - back to VALID
                Backend->Backend: [AUDIT LOG] eventType = REVOCATION_FASTPATH_REACTIVATE
            end
            Backend->Backend: [AUDIT LOG] Store revocation rejected\neventType = REVOCATION_REJECTED , rejectReason , actionBy
            Backend->App: Notify - request REJECTED + reason (may re-request later)
            note over App,Backend #pink: Outcome = NO REVOKE (request closed)
        else Issuer APPROVES
            note over Admin,Backend #lightgreen: decidedAction = REVOKE -> proceed to SHARED below
        end
    end
end

==  SHARED : CORE APPLIES STATUS CHANGE + PUBLISH STATUS LIST  ==
alt An action was decided (Case A: transition allowed  OR  Case B: issuer approved)

    note over Backend,Core #orange: SHARED. Core applies the status change + publishes Status List
    note over Backend,Core #wheat:[SPEC] Reached ONLY when an action was decided\nReject / invalid paths above end without reaching here

    Backend->Core: Apply action\n(POST /api/credential/v1/{id}/{revoke | suspend | reactivate})
    Core->Core: Set / Clear status bit at statusListIndex
    Core->Core: Serialize Status List\nbitstring -> gzip + base64 (reflecting the new bit)
    Core->HSM: Sign updated Status List Credential (JWS)\nwith issuer signing key
    HSM-->Core: Issuer signature
    Core->Core: Re-publish at the SAME /ssi/revocation/v1/list/{id} (Core-hosted)
    Core->Core: Self-check published list is reachable\nGET /ssi/revocation/v1/list/{id} (expect HTTP 200, valid JWS)
    Core-->Backend: New status (REVOKED / SUSPENDED / VALID) , statusListIndex , effectiveAt

    alt Core or Status List publish failed
        Backend->Backend: [ERROR AUDIT] Store failure\nfailureStep = CORE_STATUS_UPDATE / STATUS_LIST_PUBLISH , errorCode , retryable
        Backend-->Admin: Action failed - please retry (status unchanged)
    else Status updated successfully
        note over Backend #lightgreen: Persist status + write audit log
        Backend->Backend: [DATA STORE] Update credential status reference\ncredentialId , status , reason , effectiveAt , suspendEndDate (if SUSPEND) , actionBy
        Backend->Backend: [AUDIT LOG] Store lifecycle audit log\neventType = CREDENTIAL_REVOKED / SUSPENDED / REACTIVATED\ncredentialId , reason , actionBy , effectiveAt , auditHash , auditSignature , previousAuditHash , retentionUntil , immutableStorage = WORM

        note over App,Backend #lightblue: Notify Holder
        Backend->App: Push notification\ncredentialId , newStatus , reason
        App->App: [DATA STORE] Update local credential metadata\nstatus = newStatus (do not change holder key / reference)
        App->App: Display updated credential status\n(revoked / suspended / active)
        Backend-->Admin: Lifecycle action completed (status , effectiveAt)
    end

else No action - request was invalid or rejected (flow already ended above)
    note over Backend #pink: No status change ; nothing further
end

note over Backend,Core #wheat:[SPEC] Effect on verification (see VP-9 section 26):\nNext VP verification fetches Status List -> REVOKED / SUSPENDED -> verification FAILS\n-> VALID (after reactivate) -> verification can pass again
note over Backend,Core #wheat:[SPEC] Scheduled auto-reactivation (optional):\nIf SUSPEND had suspendEndDate, a scheduler reactivates at that time (re-runs REACTIVATE)
note over Admin,App #wheat:[SPEC] Standards mapping\nHolder right to request -> NIST 800-63B (invalidation) , PDPA s.19/33 , eIDAS user control\nIssuer authority to decide -> W3C VC 2.0 (issuer controls status) , ETDA Trust Framework\nFast-path on loss/theft -> NIST 800-63B (immediate invalidation)\nSLA + mandatory reject reason -> PDPA / GDPR\nStatus list mechanism -> W3C Bitstring Status List (see Lifecycle-2)\nAudit at every step -> PDPA s.39 accountability , ISO 27001

@enduml